Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Front-End Web Developer position with You.com. I bring over three years of professional experience in front-end web development, responsive design, and user-focused interface creation, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across three engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade web applications that directly reflect the design and development expertise this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and built responsive, visually appealing landing pages using React, JavaScript, and HTML/CSS with cross-browser compatibility and accessibility standards, improving engagement across 1000+ platform endpoints. I developed performance-optimized front-end solutions through code optimization and SEO best practices, reducing page load times by 60% while maintaining brand alignment — demonstrating the balance between visual design and technical performance that this role requires. I collaborated closely with marketing and content teams to translate designs into clean, scalable, maintainable code, ensuring seamless content updates and consistent user experiences, and built content management workflows enabling non-technical teams to efficiently update web content — directly mirroring the collaborative, marketing-focused responsibilities central to this role. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I built user-friendly web applications using React and JavaScript, collaborating with design teams to deliver high-quality, visually appealing web experiences aligned with brand guidelines. I developed file management interfaces applying responsive design principles and performance optimization, and contributed to front-end development of an Identity & Access Management platform using React supporting thousands of users, ensuring accessibility and cross-browser compatibility. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to You.com's marketing team and deliver high-performing, user-focused web experiences.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in visual design, user experience optimization, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the design-development hybrid approach this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I created responsive web interfaces for AI model deployment using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Figma, ensuring optimal user experience and performance across devices. I was responsible for the full design-to-implementation lifecycle — from creating design mockups in Figma to writing production-ready front-end code — ensuring both visual appeal and technical excellence. Beyond building the interfaces myself, I designed and delivered workshops on front-end development and AI tools for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the collaboration and communication responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into a developer who designs with creativity and builds with precision, both of which I would bring to You.com's marketing team.

I have always been passionate about building trusted, accurate, and user-focused AI systems and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of You.com's mission to create the AI Search Infrastructure that powers modern AI. Your commitment to facts-first decision making, collaborative culture, and recognition for meaningful impact resonates deeply with my approach to web development and teamwork. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

